tldr: The user requested a thorough aesthetic review and improvement of their
  sleep questionnaire app. I implemented a new sleep-themed color palette,
  redesigned key components like the progress bar and intro section, and updated
  form elements and section groupings for a more polished and calming user
  experience.
overview: The user wanted to transform their sleep questionnaire app's
  aesthetics from a basic, functional design to a more beautiful and engaging
  experience. I began by analyzing the existing CSS and component styling,
  identifying areas like the generic color palette, plain backgrounds, and
  uninspired form elements. My approach involved a multi-step refinement
  process. First, I introduced a sophisticated sleep-themed color palette with
  deep indigos, purples, and teal accents, along with custom utility classes for
  gradients and shadows. I then redesigned the main  layout,
  adding subtle background blurs and a more engaging progress indicator. The
   was transformed into a welcoming hero section with interactive
  feature cards and improved alerts. Key UI components like checkboxes, radio
  buttons, and sliders were polished with larger sizes, rounded corners, and
  better hover states. Crucially, I updated the section grouping styles across
  the entire app, replacing generic gray boxes with refined, card-style elements
  to ensure visual consistency. After an initial set of changes, a browser
  review prompted a further sweep to update remaining sections that still used
  older styling. The outcome is an app with a calming, professional, and
  cohesive aesthetic, tailored specifically for a sleep health assessment.
